<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1932-06-27T05:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1932-06-27T05:00:00-05:00" n="156" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d156">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">500.A15A4/1186: Telegram</note>
                            <head>
                                <hi rend="italic">The Acting Chairman of the American Delegation
                                        (<persName corresp="#p_GHS1" type="from">Gibson</persName>)
                                    to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                                </hi>
                            </head>
                            <opener>
                                <dateline rendition="#right">
                                    <placeName>
                                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Geneva</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1932-06-27T11:00:00+01:00">June
                                        27, 1932—11 a.m.</date>
                                    <lb/> [Received June 27—5:43 a.m.]</dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p>279. My telegram No. 278, June 26, 6 p.m. Correspondents at Lausanne
                                were informed from British sources yesterday afternoon of my meeting
                                with <persName corresp="#p_MJR1">MacDonald</persName> though no
                                details were revealed.</p>
                            <closer>
                                <signed>
                                    <persName corresp="#p_GHS1">
                                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Gibson</hi>
                                    </persName>
                                </signed>
                            </closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>